2026-05-19 | Minimum Common Value in Two Sorted Arrays

	Question
Return minimum common integer.
	Key Insight
Since arrays are already sorted:
		use two pointers efficiently.
At every step:
- smaller value cannot be common later
- move its pointer forward
	Approach
1.	Initialize:
		i = 0
		j = 0
2.	While both pointers valid:
		if nums1[i] == nums2[j]:
				return nums1[i]
		else if nums1[i] < nums2[j]:
				i++
		else:
				j++
3.	If traversal ends:
		return -1
	Time Complexity
	O(n + m)
	Space Complexity
	O(1)
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    int getCommon(vector<int>& nums1, vector<int>& nums2) {
        int i = 0;
        int j = 0;
        while(i < nums1.size() && j < nums2.size()){
            if(nums1[i] == nums2[j])
                return nums1[i];
            if(nums1[i] < nums2[j])
                i++;
            else
                j++;
        }
        return -1;
    }
};
	Key Insight
Sorted arrays allow:
		linearly finding intersection
		using two pointers  
This avoids unnecessary nested loops.
